The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index rose 0.3 percent to 63,691.18.  CCR SA (CCRO3)  (CCRO3 BS) gained 1 percent to 15.65 reais. The
toll-road operator said a unit agreed to pay 72 million reais
($39.5 million) to acquire 80 percent of Barcas SA - Transportes
Maritimos, according to a regulatory filing.  Telecomunicacoes Brasileiras SA (TELB4)  (TELB4 BS) fell 0.1 percent
to 13.69 reais, after earlier losing as much as 0.7 percent. The
state-controlled telecommunications company known as Telebras
said its board approved a 300 million reais  capital increase by
selling new shares.  Homebuilders gained as traders bet a slowdown in inflation
last month will prompt  Brazil â€™s central bank to keep cutting
benchmark  interest rates .  MRV Engenharia e Participacoes SA 
(MRVE3 BS) gained 3.7 percent to 13.67 reais.  Rossi Residencial
SA (RSID3)  (RSID3 BS) rose 2.8 percent to 10.15 reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
